commentary: Mujeeb Ur Rahman to Gayle, OUT Mujeeb's bag of tricks has bamboozled Gayle. This is a googly that pitches on middle and off, spins just a wee bit to beat the outside edge, clip the top of the back pad and hit off stump. Gayle and Mujeeb could well be training together a lot from April at the IPL, for now, he'll have to simply walk back.

commentary: Gulbadin Naib to Samuels, OUT steers this to point as they take off for a suicidal single. This is superb from Najibullah Zadran, who runs quickly to his left, picks up the ball and fires a direct hit to leave Lewis high and dry. He wasn't even in the frame, wasn't running too fast either, especially with the left glove in his hands. This is very poor from West Indies, but outstanding athleticism from Zadran.

Nabi absolutely nailed the pull and he now walks off in disbelief.

commentary: Paul to Sharafuddin Ashraf, FOUR runs those are the winning runs. Afghanistan live to fight another day. West Indies, unbeaten until today, have been brought to their knees. This should give Afghanistan so much confidence, such a big boost. That's one out of three. Nervy alright, but they still got the job done in the end. The man to thank with the bat: Rahmat Shah.
